She talks SO fast but repeats herself often. If you print the slides its pretty helpful. She explains everything really well but orgo is overall a super hard class and requires A LOT of effort. If you actually want to do well in this class prioritize it over everything.

Attendance is required unless you have a friend to take notes. "All the notes" are available on brightspace, except some words that you have to add and the mechanisms with the arrows. She talks really fast so you can barely understand anything and she can be unpleasant most of the time. Usually only one question about nomenclature on tests.

This class will ask alot of you mentally. You have to be determined and have as strong work ethic. Don't assume that because you did well in orgo 1 last year that this class will be easy. You have to put in the work (doing lots of practice problems). Your final grade will reflect the amount of practice you had.

Amazing prof. For her first year teaching she really did a great job. Super enthusiastic about the content, very friendly and approachable. Her explanations make sense and are clear and precise. She does speak pretty fast but you slowly kind of get used to it, she's also super conscious about that and does her best to improve. Love her!
Awesome class, very clear explanations. She talks fast, but if you are remotely intelligent you will be able to follow. She is an excellent professor.

This prof tends to talk fast; however, if you print the notes and fill them in by what she writes on the screen they make sense. It is expected that you remember all previous courses, i.e. basic general chemistry and Organic one. If you have forgotten things, you will fail!!!! Ask her to talk slower, and she'll slow down, a little-look at screen
